<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Discretion" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Discretion,</orth> 1) good sense, common sense, reason, wisdom: <cit><quote>I will not adventure my d. so weakly,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.1.188" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 1, 188</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I have need of such a youth that can with some d. do my business,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.4.70" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. IV, 4, 70</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>nor do I think the man of safe d. that does affect it,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 1.1.72" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 1, 72</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ado 2.3.198" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 3, 198</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.1.78" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 1, 78</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.734" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 734</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.1.235" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 1, 235</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.1.235" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 1, 235</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.1.235" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 1, 235</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.1.235" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 1, 235</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.1.235" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 1, 235</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mv 3.5.70" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 5, 70</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 5.4.121" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A V, 4, 121</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 2.4.38" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 4, 38</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.1.158" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A IV, 1, 158</bibl> <cit><quote>(--s).</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 1.1.50" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 1, 50</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. h8 5.3.137" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 137</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 1.2.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 2, 24</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 1.2.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 2, 24</bibl> <bibl n="shak. cor 1.1.206" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 1, 206</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.2.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 2, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 2.1.117" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 117</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 2.2.489" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 489</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.2.19" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 2.4.151" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. II, 4, 151</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.7.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 7, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 1.3.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 3, 5</bibl>. Misapplied by Evans: <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.1.44" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 1, 44</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.1.44" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 1, 44</bibl> <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.4.1" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 1</bibl>.<lb />2) becoming regard, consideration: <cit><quote>old folks, you know, have d., as they say, and know the world,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.2.135" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. II, 2, 135</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>they would have no more d. but to hang us,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 1.2.83" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. I, 2, 83</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>you do not use me with that affability as in d. you ought to use me,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 3.2.139" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 2, 139</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>let's teach ourselves that honourable stop, not to outsport d.</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 2.3.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 3, 3</bibl></cit>.
<lb /><emph>Use thy d.</emph> == use thy pleasure, <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.1.152" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 1, 152</bibl>. <cit><quote>well, do your d.</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 3.3.34" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 3, 34</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>